  "prompt": "How should I study for bank PO?",
  "response": "To prepare for Bank PO (Probationary Officer) exams, follow these strategies:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Familiarize yourself with syllabus\n- Know sections: Quantitative Aptitude, Reasoning, English, General Awareness\n- Understand marking scheme and time management\n\n2. Study Material\n- IBPS/SBI PO previous year question papers\n- Standard reference books\n- Online study materials\n- Mock test series\n\n3. Quantitative Aptitude\n- Practice arithmetic\n- Work on data interpretation\n- Learn shortcut techniques\n- Solve problems quickly and accurately\n\n4. Reasoning\n- Practice puzzles and logical reasoning\n- Blood relations\n- Coding-decoding\n- Series completion\n- Syllogism\n\n5. English\n- Improve vocabulary\n- Practice grammar\n- Reading comprehension\n- Para jumbles\n- Error spotting\n\n6. General Awareness\n- Read newspapers daily\n- Follow current affairs\n- Study banking awareness\n- Economic news\n- National and international events\n\n7. Additional Preparation Tips\n- Create a structured study plan\n- Take regular mock tests\n- Analyze your performance\n- Work on weak areas\n- Develop time management skills\n\n8. Online Resources\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Online test platforms\n- Banking exam preparation websites\n\nConsistent practice and strategic preparation are key to success.",
